read
> Old English rǣdan, of Germanic origin; related to Dutch raden and German raten 'advise, guess'. Early senses included 'advise' and 'interpret (a riddle or dream') (see rede)
rede vt. 忠告，解开（谜），说故事; n. 计划; 解释; 传说;